{"title_page": "2010s in Iraq political history", "text_new": "'''2010s in Iraq political history'''  is an overview of significant politicial and societal historical events in Iraq during the 2010s.\n\n{{Year nav topic5|2019|Iraq}}\n\n\n==General history (Early to mid-2010s)==\n{{expand section|date=December 2019}}\n\n==General history (Late 2010s)==\n{{also|2019 Iraqi protests}}\n\nThe [[2019 Iraqi protests]], also nicknamed the Tishreen Revolution<ref>{{cite web|url=https://iraqakhbar.com/2084791|title=\u062b\u0648\u0631\u0629 \u062a\u0634\u0631\u064a\u0646 \u2026\u0648\u0637\u0645\u0648\u062d\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0628\u0627\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0634\u0631\u0648\u0639\u0629|language=Arabic|trans-title=The October Revolution{{nbsp}}... and the legitimate ambitions of young people|website=News of Iraq|accessdate=15 November 2019|date=12 November 2019}}</ref> and 2019 Iraqi Intifada, are an ongoing series of protests that consisted of [[Demonstration (political)|demonstrations]], [[marches]], [[sit-ins]] and [[civil disobedience]]. They started on 1{{nbsp}}October 2019, a date which was set by civil activists on social media, spreading over the central and southern provinces of Iraq, to protest 16 years of corruption, unemployment and inefficient public services, before they escalated into calls to overthrow the administration and to stop [[Iranian intervention in Iraq (2014\u2013present)|Iranian intervention in Iraq]]. The Iraqi government has been accused of using bullets, snipers, hot water and [[tear gas]] against protesters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/10/iraq-hrw-denounces-lethal-force-protesters-urges-probe-191010123643525.html|title=Iraq: HRW denounces lethal force against protesters, urges probe|website=aljazeera.com}}</ref> Prime Minister [[Adil Abdul-Mahdi]] announced on 29 November that he would resign.<ref name=Resignation29Nov>{{Cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2019/11/29/iraq-prime-minister-resign-worsening-crisis-074396|title=Iraqi prime minister to resign in wake of deadly protests|work=[[Associated Press]]|date=29 November 2019|accessdate=29 November 2019}}</ref> According to the [[BBC]], they call for the end of the political system which has existed since [[2003 invasion of Iraq|the US-led invasion]] ousted [[Saddam Hussein]] and has been marked by sectarian divides.<ref name=\"bbc\">{{cite news| url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-49960677 | work=BBC News | title=Iraq protests: What's behind the anger?| date=7 October 2019 | accessdate=27 October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"guardiansaddam\">{{cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/oct/27/iraq-protests-aim-topple-regime | work=[[The Guardian]]| title='They are worse than Saddam': Iraqis take to streets to topple regime| date=27 October 2019 | accessdate=28 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://providencemag.com/2019/11/iraq-protests/|title=An Iraq for All Iraqis?|date=2019-11-26|website=Providence|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref> It is the largest unrest since the Saddam Hussein government concluded.<ref name=\"larges\">{{cite news| url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2019/11/07/why-iraqs-protesters-are-still-in-the-streets | work=[[Foreign Policy]] | title=Iraq Protester's Step Up Their Tactics As the Government in Baghdad Scrambles to Respond | date=7 November 2019 | accessdate=18 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe UN Envoy for Iraq,  [[Jeanine Hennis-Plasschaert]], called for renewed efforts to restore civil balance and protections for free speech. <ref> [https://news.un.org/en/story/2019/12/1052641 Protests and civil unrest show \u2018renewed sense of patriotism\u2019 in Iraq, UN envoy tells Security Council], UN.org., December 3, 2019. </ref> <ref> [https://news.un.org/en/story/2019/12/1053011 Denouncing attacks against Baghdad protesters, UN warns \u2018violence risks placing Iraq on dangerous trajectory], December 7, 2019. </REF>\n\n==History by issue==\n{{expand section|date=December 2019}}\n\n==History by government agency==\n{{expand section|date=December 2019}}\n\n==History by region==\n{{expand section|date=December 2019}}\n\n\n==See also==\n* [[2010s political history]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{iraq-hist-stub}}\n\n[[Category:2010s in Iraq]]\n[[Category:Politics overviews by decade]]\n[[Category:2010 in politics]]\n", "text_old": "'''2010s in Iraq political history'''  is an overview of significant politicial and societal historical events in Iraq during the 2010s.\n\n{{Year nav topic5|2019|Iraq}}\n\n\n==General history (Early to mid-2010s)==\n{{expand section|date=December 2019}}\n\n==General history (Late 2010s)==\n{{also|2019 Iraqi protests}}\n\nThe [[2019 Iraqi protests]], also nicknamed the Tishreen Revolution<ref>{{cite web|url=https://iraqakhbar.com/2084791|title=\u062b\u0648\u0631\u0629 \u062a\u0634\u0631\u064a\u0646 \u2026\u0648\u0637\u0645\u0648\u062d\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0628\u0627\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0634\u0631\u0648\u0639\u0629|language=Arabic|trans-title=The October Revolution{{nbsp}}... and the legitimate ambitions of young people|website=News of Iraq|accessdate=15 November 2019|date=12 November 2019}}</ref> and 2019 Iraqi Intifada, are an ongoing series of protests that consisted of [[Demonstration (political)|demonstrations]], [[marches]], [[sit-ins]] and [[civil disobedience]]. They started on 1{{nbsp}}October 2019, a date which was set by civil activists on social media, spreading over the central and southern provinces of Iraq, to protest 16 years of corruption, unemployment and inefficient public services, before they escalated into calls to overthrow the administration and to stop [[Iranian intervention in Iraq (2014\u2013present)|Iranian intervention in Iraq]]. The Iraqi government has been accused of using bullets, snipers, hot water and [[tear gas]] against protesters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/10/iraq-hrw-denounces-lethal-force-protesters-urges-probe-191010123643525.html|title=Iraq: HRW denounces lethal force against protesters, urges probe|website=aljazeera.com}}</ref> Prime Minister [[Adil Abdul-Mahdi]] announced on 29 November that he would resign.<ref name=Resignation29Nov>{{Cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2019/11/29/iraq-prime-minister-resign-worsening-crisis-074396|title=Iraqi prime minister to resign in wake of deadly protests|work=[[Associated Press]]|date=29 November 2019|accessdate=29 November 2019}}</ref> According to the [[BBC]], they call for the end of the political system which has existed since [[2003 invasion of Iraq|the US-led invasion]] ousted [[Saddam Hussein]] and has been marked by sectarian divides.<ref name=\"bbc\">{{cite news| url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-49960677 | work=BBC News | title=Iraq protests: What's behind the anger?| date=7 October 2019 | accessdate=27 October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"guardiansaddam\">{{cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/oct/27/iraq-protests-aim-topple-regime | work=[[The Guardian]]| title='They are worse than Saddam': Iraqis take to streets to topple regime| date=27 October 2019 | accessdate=28 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://providencemag.com/2019/11/iraq-protests/|title=An Iraq for All Iraqis?|date=2019-11-26|website=Providence|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref> It is the largest unrest since the Saddam Hussein government concluded.<ref name=\"larges\">{{cite news| url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2019/11/07/why-iraqs-protesters-are-still-in-the-streets | work=[[Foreign Policy]] | title=Iraq Protester's Step Up Their Tactics As the Government in Baghdad Scrambles to Respond | date=7 November 2019 | accessdate=18 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe UN Envoy for Iraq,  [[Jeanine Hennis-Plasschaert]], called for renewed efforts to restore civil balance and protections for free speech. <ref> [https://news.un.org/en/story/2019/12/1052641 Protests and civil unrest show \u2018renewed sense of patriotism\u2019 in Iraq, UN envoy tells Security Council], UN.org., December 3, 2019. </ref> <ref> [https://news.un.org/en/story/2019/12/1053011 Denouncing attacks against Baghdad protesters, UN warns \u2018violence risks placing Iraq on dangerous trajectory], December 7, 2019. </REF>\n\n==History by issue==\n{{expand section|date=December 2019}}\n\n==History by government agency==\n{{expand section|date=December 2019}}\n\n==History by region==\n{{expand section|date=December 2019}}\n\n\n==See also==\n* [[2010s political history]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{iraq-hist-stub}}\n\n[[Category:2010s in Iraq]]\n[[Category:Politics overviews by decade]]\n", "name_user": "Fayenatic london", "label": "safe", "comment": "Copying fromCategory:Politics overviews by decadetoCategory:2010 in politicsusingCat-a-lot", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2010s_in_Iraq_political_history"}
